# dist/ is the locally built SPA. The `deno task deploy` flow builds it, uploads it
# via `deno deploy --source local`, then deletes it again, so it normally doesn't exist
# in your working tree. It must NOT be gitignored during that upload window (the uploader
# respects .gitignore), so we re-include it here (the repo-root .gitignore ignores all `dist`).
!dist/
!dist/**
client/node_modules/
node_modules/
.env
.deno/
